# E2E test environment — copy to .env.test and fill in real values.
# Run: make e2e-up && make e2e-run
#
# ── What runs by default ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# docker-compose.test.yml hardcodes RELAYS=ibkr, so the IBKR relay is
# always loaded in the E2E stack. No extra config needed for:
#   - test_health_ok          (GET /health)
#   - test_auth_required      (POST /relays/ibkr/poll/1 without token → 401)
#
# ── Listener E2E (opt-in) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# These tests verify the real-time WS listener receives fills from
# ibkr_bridge. They SKIP (not fail) when the bridge is unavailable.
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. ibkr_bridge running locally:  cd ../ibkr_bridge && make local-up
#   2. IB Gateway connected (paper account)
#   3. Set the three IBKR_BRIDGE_* vars below and LISTENER_ENABLED=true
#
# IBKR_BRIDGE_WS_URL        — used by the relay container to connect to bridge WS
#                              (host.docker.internal resolves to the Docker host)
# IBKR_BRIDGE_API_BASE_URL  — used by pytest (host-side) to place orders via bridge
# IBKR_BRIDGE_API_TOKEN     — must match ibkr_bridge's API_TOKEN
LISTENER_ENABLED=false
# IBKR_BRIDGE_WS_URL=ws://host.docker.internal:15101/ibkr/ws/events
# IBKR_BRIDGE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:15101
# IBKR_BRIDGE_API_TOKEN=your_bridge_api_token
